# DESCRIPTION
# Skills building problem
# ENDDESCRIPTION

## DBsubject(Trigonometry)
## DBchapter(Analytic trigonometry)
## DBsection(Solving trigonometric equations exactly)
## Level(2)
## KEYWORDS('trigonometric equation')

DOCUMENT();
loadMacros("PGstandard.pl",
           "MathObjects.pl",
           "PGML.pl",
	   "parserPopUp.pl",
# "PGchoicemacros.pl",
# "PGgraphmacros.pl",
# "parserNumberWithUnits.pl",
# "parserFormulaWithUnits.pl", 
# "parserFormulaUpToConstant.pl",
# "PGcourse.pl",
);

Context("Numeric");
Context()->functions->disable("Trig");
Context()->flags->set( tolerance => 0.000000001 );

@fracs = ( "-\frac{\sqrt3}2", "-\frac12", "\frac12", "\frac{\sqrt3}2" );
$aind = random(0,3,1);
$bind = random(0,3,1);

$a = $fracs[$aind];
$b = $fracs[$bind];

$c = list_random( 0, 2 );

$k1 = random(2,5,1);
$k2 = random(1,6,1);
$k3 = random(2,4,1);

if ( $bind == 0 ) {
    $asol = "$k1*5*pi/6 + $k2";
    $phi = "\frac{5\pi}6";
    ($n,$d) = reduce( 5*$k1, 6 );
    $k1c = ( $d == 1 ) ? "$n" : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
} elsif ( $bind == 1 ) {
    $asol = "$k1*2*pi/3 + $k2";
    $phi = "\frac{2\pi}3";
    ($n,$d) = reduce( 2*$k1, 3 );
    $k1c = ( $d == 1 ) ? "$n" : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
} elsif ( $bind == 2 ) {
    $asol = "$k1*pi/3 + $k2";
    $phi = "\frac{\pi}3";
    ($n,$d) = reduce( $k1, 3 );
    $k1c = ( $d == 1 ) ? "$n" : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
} else {
    $asol = "$k1*pi/6 + $k2";
    $phi = "\frac{\pi}6";
    ($n,$d) = reduce( $k1, 6 );
    $k1c = ( $d == 1 ) ? "$n" : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
}

if ( $c == 0 ) {
    $bsol = "(3*$k3 - 1)*pi";
    $bphi = "\frac{3\pi}2";
    $ssol = (3*$k3 - 1) . "\pi";
} else {
    $bsol = "($k3 - 1)*pi";
    $bphi = "\frac{\pi}2";
    $ssol = ($k3 == 2) ? "\pi" : ($k3 - 1) . "\pi";
}

TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_PGML

Taking all arguments of the given trigonometric functions to lie in
[`[0, 2\pi)`], find exact solutions to each of the following equations.
Your solutions should be in terms of explict real numbers, not
trigonometric functions.

a. [`` \cos\left(\frac{x - [$k2]}{[$k1]}\right) = [$b] ``]  
[`x = `] [___]{$asol}{10}

b. [`` \sin\left(\frac{x + \pi}{[$k3*2]}\right) + 1 = [$c] ``]  
[`x = `] [___]{$bsol}{10}

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

a. Note that [`\cos(\phi) = [$b]`] when [`\phi = [$phi]`].  Thus
[`\frac{x - [$k2]}{[$k1]} = [$phi]`], so that [`x = [$k1c]\pi + [$k2]`].

b. Similarly, letting [`\phi = \frac{x + \pi}{[$k3*2]}`], we need
[`\sin(\phi) = [$c-1].`]  This occurs when [`\phi = [$bphi]`], so that
[`x = [$ssol]`].

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
